🚀 1. Snooping Mechanism (Deep Dive)
🧠 Core Idea
👉 All caches listen to a shared communication medium (bus/interconnect)

🔥 Think like this:
“Every cache hears everything”

⚙️ How it works (step-by-step)
Scenario: Core 1 writes X
Step 1: Core 1 issues request
BusRdX (Read for ownership)
Address = X
Step 2: Broadcast
👉 This goes to:
All other caches
Step 3: All caches snoop (monitor)
Each cache checks:
Do I have X
Step 4: Reaction
If yes:
Invalidate OR
Provide data
Step 5: Core 1 gets ownership
👉 Moves to Modified (M)
🧠 Hardware View
Each cache has:
Snoop logic
Tag lookup on snoop requests


⚠️ Limitation of Snooping
❌ Problem: Broadcast traffic
👉 Every request:
Sent to ALL cores
❌ Problem: Scalability
👉 Works well for:
2–8 cores
👉 Breaks for:
32+ cores
| Feature       | Value     |
| ------------- | --------- |
| Communication | Broadcast |
| Latency       | Low       |
| Complexity    | Simple    |
| Scalability   | Poor      |
